  lectureDescription: "<h1>Lecture Summary: Game Visual Manager and Spawning Objects</h1><p>In
    this lecture, we created a <strong>GameVisualManager </strong>class to handle
    visual elements like spawning crosses and circles, ensuring a <strong>clean separation
    </strong>of logic and visuals. Following best practices, we made the visuals
    child objects of empty parent game objects, keeping things organized.</p><p>We
    used <strong>events </strong>to decouple the GameManager from the GameVisualManager,
    triggering visual updates when a grid position was clicked. A helper function
    converted grid positions to world positions for correctly placing objects.</p><p>For
    multiplayer synchronization, we added a <strong>NetworkObject </strong>component
    to the prefabs and called the <strong>Spawn() </strong>function to ensure objects
    were synchronized across all clients. However, only the server can spawn objects,
    enforcing server authority which is a key concept in multiplayer game development.
    We\u2019ll explore how to handle client-to-server communication using <strong>RPCs
    </strong>in the next lecture.</p>\r\n<p>What is the DIFFERENCE between Transform
    and GameObject? (Unity Tutorial for Beginners) <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B-dVf9wUEbg\"
    target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B-dVf9wUEbg</a></p><p>C# Course
